Philosophy of love is the field of [[social philosophy]] and [[ethics]] that attempts to [[explanation|explain]] the nature of love. The philosophical investigation of love includes the tasks of distinguishing between the various kinds of personal love, asking if and how love is or can be justified, asking what the [[value (ethics)|value]] of love is, and what impact love has on the [[autonomy]] of both the lover and the beloved.
